product>>description: Marchesa’s sister-line, Marchesa Notte, continues to exhibit the brand’s dedication to show-stopping flourishes, noteworthy attention to detail and feminine glamour. This stunning powder blue dress is from the label’s AW17 pre-collection, inspired by the idea of all-night dance attire. It features a figure-flattering corseted top with a sweetheart neckline, a rear zip fastening, a fitted waist and adjustable shoulder straps. The flared skirt boasts a dramatically curved high-low hemline while the body is adorned with multicoloured embroidered flowers.
Gold-tone floral embroidered gown from Marchesa Notte featuring a plunging neck, a sleeveless design, a rear zip fastening, a fitted waist and a long length.

Named after the heiress and muse Marchesa Luisa Casati who was so fabulous she walked her two pet leopards on diamond leashes, Marchesa creates magical pieces for the modern day princess. Nothing to wear to the ball, Cinderella? Don't worry, the fairy tale designs of Keren Craig and Georgina have got you covered. A subtle sweetheart curved neckline, sculpted bodice, embroidered details and full tulle skirt make this dress fit for royalty. Intricate embroidered floral filigree details trail over the corset of the gown into a dropped waist, flowing into the ultimately feminine hazy full tulle skirt. Have your regal moment in a dress that was built for twirling around a dance floor.

Marchesa’s sister-line, Marchesa Notte, continues to exhibit the brand’s dedication to show-stopping flourishes, noteworthy attention to detail and feminine glamour. This stunning black net dress is from the label’s AW17 pre-collection, inspired by the idea of all-night dance attire. It features a figure-flattering corseted top with a sweetheart neckline, a rear zip fastening, a fitted waist and adjustable shoulder straps. The flared skirt boasts a dramatically curved high-low hemline while the body is adorned with multicoloured embroidered flowers.
Bay green furry pool slides from Fenty X Puma.
Light blue cotton blend distressed skinny jeans from Amiri featuring a button and zip fly, a five pocket design, a cropped length, zip cuffs and distressed effects.
Brown sable and silk panelled fur coat from Simonetta Ravizza.

Marchesa’s sister-line, Marchesa Notte, continues to exhibit the brand’s dedication to show-stopping flourishes, noteworthy attention to detail and feminine glamour. This stunning powder blue gown is from the label’s AW17 pre-collection, inspired by the idea of all-night dance attire. It features a figure-flattering corseted top with a sweetheart neckline, a rear zip fastening, a fitted waist and adjustable shoulder straps. The flared skirt boasts a floor-skimming length while the body is adorned with multicoloured embroidered flowers.
Off-white embroidered flared gown from Oscar de la Renta.
Green and black rose embroidered gown from Marchesa Notte featuring a round neck, three-quarter length sleeves, a concealed rear zip fastening, a flared style and a long length.
Blush nude floral embroidered long dress from Marchesa Notte featuring a scoop neck, three-quarter length sleeves, a sheer construction, a waistband, a rear zip fastening and a pleated hem.
Blue artificial leather 'Elyse' lace-up shoes from Stella McCartney featuring a square toe, a lace-up front fastening, glitter details, a high wedge heel and a ridged rubber sole.
Black stretch cotton ripped skinny jeans from Saint Laurent featuring a button & zip fastening, belt loops and a five pocket design.
Champagne floral bead embellished gown from Marchesa Notte featuring a sleeveless design, a rear zip fastening, a pleated skirt, a long length and cross-over straps at the chest.

Givenchy’s red leather Shark Lock boots are a stand-out design for the luxury French fashion house. Cut for a mid-calf fit, this pair features an almond toe, a concealed side zip fastening, a foldover top panel with a silver-tone shark tooth motif twist-lock fastening and a high wedge heel.
Cream silk half-placket blouse from Stella McCartney featuring a striped pattern, a front button placket, a round neck and long sleeves.

Black and white stretch silk blend polka dot midi dress from Dolce & Gabbana featuring a square neck, a polka dot pattern, a fitted waist, ruffled sleeves, a v-back, a rear zip fastening and a knee length.

Marchesa’s sister-line, Marchesa Notte, continues to exhibit the brand’s dedication to show-stopping flourishes, noteworthy attention to detail and feminine glamour. This layered lace gown is from the label’s AW17 pre-collection, inspired by the idea of all-night dance attire. It has been immaculately fashioned from voluminous white tulle, boasting a v-neckline, a sleeveless design, a rear zip fastening, a fitted waist, a delicately scalloped lace trimming and a long-length skirt with a dramatic tiered effect.
Tan and pink asymmetric hem floral dress from Marchesa Notte.

Black and gold silk floral embroidered shift dress from Givenchy featuring a round neck, a sleeveless design, a shift silhouette, an embroidered floral design, a concealed rear zip fastening, a knee length and a rear central vent.

DSQUARED2's AW17 collection was inspired by hiking attire and the Canadian winter, with the designers taking their quirky styling out to the slopes for what the Caten twins call 'glamourous mountaineering'. This bold orange K-Way pullover jacket from DSQUARED2 features wide lapels, a hood with toggle fastenings, a front zip, a K-Way print at the chest, two front pockets, a front zip pocket and long sleeves with a printed logo to the right sleeve.
Grey cotton, leather and rubber eyelet detail sneakers from Michael Michael Kors.

Designed to link the gap between streetwear and high-end fashion, Off-White features pieces that look lived in and that are made for all-day wear. Expertly constructed from black leather, these "For Walking" knee-high boots from Off-White feature a pointed toe, a slip-on style, a print to the side and a high stiletto heel.

Combining silhouettes and design ideas in a collage-inspired manner, this motorcycle jacket functions as a showcase for the Proenza Schouler aesthetic. Crafted in Italy from a washed Italian lambskin, this dense yet soft piece has an overlapping cape-style lapel that contrasts against the fitted buttoned collar and structured back. An asymmetrical design, this directional take on the tough-luxe trend features long sleeves with decorative stitching and zipper cuff details with attached logo lanyards. 100% genuine lamb shearling. Made in Italy.
product>>name: Leather Belted Moto Jacket with Shearling Panel

product>>description: Enter the world of fabulous luxury and everlasting ease with these black logo print track pants from Marcelo Burlon County of Milan. Crafted from cotton, they feature an elasticated waistband with a drawstring fastening, side pockets and a print to the side.

Olivier Rousteing implements a ‘more is more’ philosophy which showed no boundaries in Balmain’s AW17 collection. Expect a visually rich line-up of opulent fabrics, daring cuts and his signature decadent embellishing. Crafted from a soft cotton blend and calf leather, this biker jacket from Balmain features classic lapels, a front zip fastening, front pockets, a cropped length and long sleeves with a lace-up detail.
Black leather platform loafers from Michael Michael Kors.

The dark composition and studded trim of this mini skirt is typically Alexander Wang, with other features including rounded stud embellishments and a ruffled hem. This skirt would match a fitted jacket and courts perfectly.

The Marni collection is all about contrast. Composed of the masculine and feminine, structured and delicate and light and sturdy, the Milanese label offers a distinctly off kilter approach to Italian glamour. These cropped straight leg trousers are crafted from black cotton-blend and feature a concealed front fastening, a raised front seam, two inset pockets to the sides and two back buttoned welt pockets. Wear yours as a foundation for clashing prints and draped silhouettes.
Add a playful vibe to your ensemble with these pink rabbit fur Logomania flip-flops from Chiara Ferragni, featuring an open toe, a flat rubber sole and signature winking eye appliqué detailing.
Black cotton printed sweatshirt from Etro.
Blue silk V neck ruffle sleeve dress from OFF WHITE.

Gothic style with a contemporary urban feel defines Mcq Alexander McQueen. The AW17 collection features sharp tailored pieces and streetwear styles with clean lines, in a dark, moody palette. This black cotton, silk blend Devoré mix hoodie from McQ Alexander Mcqueen features a hood with drawstring tie fastenings, long sleeves, a ribbed hem and cuffs and velvet floral embroidery.
Gold-tone leather Clover loafers from Giuseppe Zanotti Design featuring a slip-on style, an almond toe and gemstone embellishments.

From lifelong classics to seasonal sensations - harness the power of accessories with the latest Michael Michael Kors collection. Equal parts cool and classy, these Copper slip-on loafers are carefully crafted from chocolate brown leather with a glossy patent finish and detailed with a gold-tone buckle. Set on a flatform sole that’s ridged for grip, this pair also features a brand embossed leather insole as well as tonal stitching around the toes and along the heel panel. Chic and easy enough for everyday, let them punctuate dresses, tailored trousers, jeans and more.

Philipp Plein's sexy urban style is evident with this Light mini dress. Featuring a sleeveless design, a concealed rear zip fastening, a cinched waist and a flared skirt, all eyes will be glued on to you at your next party. An embellished pointed collar makes this dress so Rock'n'Roll.

Continuing the legacy of Consuelo Castiglioni, Francesco Risso creates wearable, yet artistic pieces under the guise of Marni. Asymmetrical lines, structured forms and eye-catching prints make up the DNA of the brand. Black virgin wool tailored culotte trousers from Marni featuring a high waist, a hook and zip fly, a wide leg, two back patch pockets and a cropped length.
Black and pink wool-cotton blend side-stripe tailored trousers from Etro.

Japanese designer Kenzo Takada launched Kenzo in Paris in 1970. Today, under the creative direction of Opening Ceremony's Humberto Leon and Carol Lim, the label is as popular as ever thanks to its refreshed aesthetic. This Kenzo two zip bomber jacket is an example of the urban edge that the fashion house embodies. Presented in an edgy black cotton blend, it features a two way zip fastening, long sleeves, a ribbed hem and cuffs and the signature Kenzo logo printed at the back. This jacket is the perfect wardrobe addition for off-duty wear.
Blue floral print dress from MSGM.

Every bit as luxurious as the label’s iconic Gommino loafers, these quilted Double T loafers from Tod’s are an easy way to inject a dose of old-school elegance into every look. The chic, menswear-inspired silhouette has a slim profile making them feel far more feminine. Crafted from sumptuous black leather, they feature a round toe, silver-tone hardware and a diamond quilted finish.

Gothic style with a contemporary urban feel defines Mcq Alexander McQueen. The AW17 collection features sharp tailored pieces and streetwear styles with clean lines, in a dark, moody palette. This black cotton eyelets detail sweatshirt from McQ Alexander Mcqueen features a ribbed round neck, dropped shoulders, long sleeves and a lace up detail.

Tory Burch’s designs often feature eclectic details, a feminine style and a bohemian luxe aesthetic. This romantic ivory-coloured silk Diana top from Tory Burch features a contrasting black banded collar with fabric ties, pleated ruffles at the collar and shoulders, long sleeves, button cuffs and a relaxed fit.

Brutally fashionable, the new edit from Rick Owens is dark, rebellious and entirely wearable. This black tank dress from Rick Owens features a sleeveless design, a round neck, raw edges and a racerback style. Pair with ankle boots for a tough look this summer.

Olivier Rousteing continues his evolution of Balmain’s classic styles into the brand’s AW17 collection and beyond. Equal amounts decorative, daring and refined, these garments are an elevation of Parisian craftsmanship. Crafted in France, these cotton mid-rise flared jeans from Balmain feature a concealed zip fastening, side slit pockets, a flared style, rear welt pockets and a long length.

Olivier Rousteing infuses his signature glamour and lavish embellishments into classic wardrobe staples, presenting a collection wearable silhouettes for the fashionable modern woman. These black Crepe Carrot trousers from Balmain feature a high rise, a relaxed fit, a tapered leg and a cropped length.

Olivier Rousteing took his signature glamorous route for Balmain’s AW17 collection, presenting rock-chic princesses with a Western edge on his new-season runway. Perfectly embodying this defined vision, this destroyed fringe jumper has been knitted in France from a luxuriously soft wool, boasting a round neck, long sleeves, fringe details and a distressed finish.
